Good call from umpire Tapan Sharma

Commentary Text: Bumrah to Mitchell Marsh, out Caught by Rohit!! Edged and gone. Massive, massive blow for DC and they are under huge pressure. Is this the rain effect on the pitch? Good length delivery just outside off stump, Bumrah has been struggling to find the edge in the powerplay all season. Now he has Marsh pushing away from the body at a ball that nips away slightly. Commentary Text: Thakur to Tim David, no run, appeal for a caught behind, but the umpire has turned it down. Pant looked excited, but the bowler wasn't that convinced. They don't take the review either. Tell you what? There was a clear outside edge, confirms UltraEdge. They should have gone for the review, because David can hurt them real bad. Was on a length outside off and Tim David got a feather to it as he felt for it outside off. Lucky escape for David! Pant looks at the replays on the giant screen and shakes his head in disappointment

team_b_11: Delhi Capitals (Playing XI): Prithvi Shaw, David Warner, Mitchell Marsh, Rishabh Pant(w/c), Sarfaraz Khan, Rovman Powell, Axar Patel, Shardul Thakur, Kuldeep Yadav, Anrich Nortje, Khaleel Ahmed
toss: Out come the players. MI in a huddle and Prithvi is out partnering with Warner. DC have their main openers back. Bit of a long chat in that MI huddle. They do want to end on a high and they have won the toss too.
